  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For GGF funds will be used to further Pesticide Action Network Africa&apos;s (PAN Africa) work on controlling malaria without DDT in Senegal, training farmers on sustainable cotton growing techniques, and serving as a resource center for groups working to eliminate endosulfan in Africa. They will develop and test alternatives to DDT and promote the methods to the government after working with 1,000 community members. They will train 200 farmers on integrated pest management and sustainable alternatives to pesticide use in cotton production as well as provide information on pesticide problems and alternatives for partner organizations on the PAN Africa website.</narrative>
